title: 2022 Alaska gubernatorial election
added: Following voter approval of Ballot Measure 2 during the 2020 elections in Alaska, this will be the first U.S. Senate election in Alaska held under the new election process. All candidates will run in an [[Nonpartisan blanket primary|all-party]], [[Open primaries in the United States|open primary]], from which the top four candidates will advance to the general election. Voters will then utilize [[ranked-choice voting]] during the general election.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Media|first=Andrew Kitchenman, KTOO and Alaska Public|date=2020-11-18|title=Alaska will have a new election system: Voters pass Ballot Measure 2|url=https://www.ktoo.org/2020/11/17/alaska-will-have-a-new-election-system-voters-pass-ballot-measure-2/|access-date=2020-11-18|website=KTOO|language=en-US}}</ref>
